      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARRHYTHMIA (10) was a beaten favourite when resuming against the boys at Bendigo last week but was just over a metre away. Draws wide but she is two from two when second-up so will be improved and showed her class by winning both the Vicbred and Breeders Crown finals last season. SENSES (2) is a lightly-raced but progressive filly who scored for the third time in just four starts with a second-up win at this circuit and distance last time. Has easily won a trial since and has the speed to take advantage of a low draw. IMA BOOTY SHAKER NZ (11) cops the visitors' draw but she has been progressing strongly in Queensland where she has put three wins together at Albion Park. FAKE FRIENDS (6) bombed the start last time but led from a similar draw to this when scoring at this circuit and distance prior so is worth another chance.",
